SampleCollectionMethod/MethodDescription: Prepare a laboratory blank sample (100 mL of steriled, non-buffered water) before leaving for the field. At the field site, collect at least 100 mL of water from the water body with a gloved hand. Close and seal the bottle. Transport the sample back on ice and perform laboratory preparation within 8 hours of sample collection.
